The paper focuses on visual analytics and unsupervised learning techniques for exploring large datasets, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The use of image feature analysis and unsupervised learning suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and machine learning (cs.LG). The mention of data volumes and complexity suggests a focus on database systems (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the application of the techniques to biomedical genomic data suggests a focus on bioinformatics (cs.SI).
